 Based on my understanding of this game, it seems to be a form of mixed-strategy game, where both players can benefit from not always making the same choice. In this case, if I stick to choosing R every time (a dominant strategy), I would lose in 67 out of 75 rounds, which means I would only earn 800$. However, if I were to choose a mixed strategy, say 42% R and 58% B, there's a chance that my opponent might adapt a similar strategy, leading to more wins and higher earnings.

In the worst-case scenario (my opponent always picks B), I would still earn approximately 1500$ over the course of 75 rounds if I stick with a 42% R and 58% B strategy. In the best case, where my opponent also adopts a mixed strategy, I could potentially earn more than 2300$.

While it's impossible to predict the exact strategy of my anonymous opponent, choosing a mixed strategy allows me to capitalize on potential mistakes or inconsistencies in their choices, maximizing my expected payoff. Therefore, I would choose a mixed strategy and append that choice as follows: {R42B58}
